mapLocationData.name: Forest Edge
mapLocationData.description: The transitional area between field and forest.

missionData.name: Resounding Aura
missionData.description: As you make your way through the countryside you begin to sense curious aura eminating from somewhere nearby.

dialogLines.dialogText: Seeking out the aura, you make your way into the tree line.
Suddenly a bird swoops down and gracefully lands in its nesting tree.
It turns and faces you, maintaining eye contact whilst it moves out on a limb in erratic finicking fashion.
"Welcome....Wanderer... Wait. No, not wanderer..... Traveler! Yes. Welcome, Traveler!"

dialographyData_onSuccess.locationDescSummary: You've found a bird returning to its nest. It...it just turned and greeted you as casually as one teahouse patron would to another...

dialogLines.dialogText: "Um...hello."
"Bewildered? A confused look. Yes!"
"Nothing makes sense... How am I even having this conversation right now?"
"Sleepers forget. Those sleeping...for seasons. Many seasons!"
"A bird...a bird it knows itself when its with the flock. Flying!...with the flock."
"A bird has seen... a flock. Your flock! It's a ....a... house. No! It's a...village! A bird's eye has seen it."
"There's a village nearby? How do I get there?"
"The birds...my flock. They will lead you...there...to the Village!"
You look down at the ground. You begin grasping onto a sense of hope. Talking to yourself you think "There will be people there. The villagers can help me. Surely they'll know what's happened to me."
"Before you fly. No! Go. Before you go...take this."
The bird tucked its beak into it's wing fold and retrieved a small wooden object. It flings the object down at your feet.
"You dropped it...back there. Running! While you were running..back there... and you dropped it."
As you bend down to pick up the wooden item it begins to glow with a neon green light. Holding it in your palm you're captivated by the light patterns shimmering beneath the surface of the bark.
This item resembles a tree knot that's been carved out of a trunk. Yet it's seemingly whole, like its own standalone organism. You feel fortified by its presence.
A bird calls loudly in the distance and you snap out of it. You store the Arbor Sigil and gaze up at the bird again. "Thank you for your help. Surely, I'd still be lost if not for you."
"They call to you...your guides.... Now fly!"

dialographyData_Pre.locationDescSummary: After a bizarre conversation with a talking bird, an event you're not even trying to justify at this point, it presented you with a gift: The Arbor Sigil. It also mentioned that you may find the answers you seek at a local village and then provided you with a means of finding it on your map.

dialogLines.dialogText: As you approach the edge of the forest you trip over something.
Turning back to look at the object jutting from the ground you spot a half buried wooden plaque. Noticing the words carved into its facade you begin reading them aloud.

"Those who roam this land may be richer than the Shogun. Some hearts are drawn to the solace of a journey through quite forests and high peaks. To those wandering souls it is said: May you all find your true paths among the many roads."
As you hear the words repeating in your mind the hairs on the back of your neck stand and a warm feeling of bliss washes over you.
As your eyes reach the signature at the bottom of the plaque you find the wood surrounding the name has been eroded, making it impossible to read the writer's name.
You place the plaque where you found it and stand back up. Poised in thought you gaze into the tree line.
As your busy mind regains focus you begin sensing a strong aura nearby.

interactionlessDialographyDatas.locationDescSummary: As you make your way down the mountainside you begin to sense curious aura eminating from somewhere nearby.
